<section xml:id="lesson-08">
  <title>Lesson 8</title>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Solve polynomial equations by factoring.</li>
      <li>Solve equations involving radicals and identify extraneous solutions.</li>
      <li>Solve equations with rational exponents.</li>
      <li>Solve rational equations and check for extraneous solutions.</li>
      <li>Apply algebraic formulas to real-world situations.</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-factoring">
    <title>Factoring Equations</title>

    <p>
      For the following exercises, solve each equation and identify any
      extraneous solutions.
    </p>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex1">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>x^3 - 2x^2 - 3x = 0</m> by factoring.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex2">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>x^3 = 4x</m> by factoring.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex3">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>x^4 - 2x^3 + 3x^2 - 6x = 0</m> by factoring.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-radicals">
    <title>Radical Equations</title>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex4">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>\sqrt{x + 1} + 5 = x - 2</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex5">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>\sqrt{2x - 5} = 1 - \sqrt{x - 3}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-rational-exponents">
    <title>Rational Exponents</title>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex6">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>v^{5/4} = 243</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex7">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>-5126 = -6 - 5(3x + 22)^{5/3}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-quadratic-forms">
    <title>Quadratic and Substitution Forms</title>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex8">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>20x^4 - 25x^2 + 5 = 0</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex9">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>(x - 2)^2 + 7(x - 2) + 12 = 0</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex10">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>x^3 = x^{3/2} + 6</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-rational-equations">
    <title>Rational Equations</title>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex11">
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>\frac{x - 3}{x + 5} = \frac{x}{x + 2}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex12">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve
          <m>\frac{x}{x + 2} + \frac{7}{x - 5} = \frac{14}{x^2 - 3x - 10}</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex13">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve
          <m>\frac{3x}{x + 4} + \frac{4x}{x - 3} = \frac{84}{x^2 + x - 12}</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex14">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve
          <m>\frac{x}{x + 4} + \frac{4}{x - 4} = \frac{x^2 + 16}{x^2 - 16}</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="l8-application">
    <title>Application</title>

    <exercise xml:id="l8-ex15">
      <statement>
        <p>
          For a spinning amusement park ride, the velocity <m>v</m> in meters
          per second of a car moving around a curve with radius <m>r</m> meters
          is given by <m>v = \sqrt{ar}</m>, where <m>a</m> is the acceleration
          in meters per second squared.
        </p>
        <ol marker="a.">
          <li>
            For safety reasons, a ride has a minimum acceleration of
            <m>30</m> <m>\text{m}/\text{s}^2</m>. If the velocity is <m>14</m> <m>\text{m}/\text{s}</m>,
            what is the minimum radius of the curve?
          </li>
          <li>
            What is the acceleration of a car moving at <m>15</m> <m>\text{m}/\text{s}</m>
            around a curve with a radius of <m>6</m> meters?
          </li>
        </ol>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </subsection>

</section>